      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/mTA",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Wenig gebraeuchliche Bezeichnung fuer den von mehreren Quertaelern durchbrochenen, bis ins Gipfelniveau (Thalerkogel, 1655 m) bewaldeten Mittelgebirgszug, der die Mur-Muerz-Furche (Oberes Murtal, Unteres und Mittleres Muerztal) von der parallel dazu verlaufenden, jedoch nur unvollstaendig entwickelten Laengstal- und Beckenflucht am Suedfuß der nordalpinen Hochgebirge (Trofaiacher und Aflenzer Becken) trennt. Der Zug besteht in seinem aeußersten W aus schwach metamorphen Gesteinen der Grauwackenzone, im Zentrum und im E hingegen aus hoehermetamorphem zentralalpinem Kristallin, innerhalb dessen im aeußersten E der hohe Anteil an karbonatischen Gesteinen (Semmeringmesozoikum) hervorzuheben ist. Die noerdliche Begrenzung hat einen komplizierten Verlauf. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Little common name for the middle mountain range, which is broken through by several transverse valleys and forested up to the summit level (Thalerkogel, 1655 m) and separates the Mur-Muerz-furrow (upper Mur valley, lower and middle Mur valley) from the parallel, but only incompletely developed longitudinal valley and basin alignment at the southern foot of the northern alpine high mountains (Trofaiacher and Aflenzer basin). The train consists in its outermost W of weakly metamorphic rocks of the greywacke zone, in the center and in the E however of higher metamorphic central alpine crystalline, within which in the outermost E the high proportion of carbonatic rocks (Semmering Mesozoic) is to be emphasized. The northern boundary has a complicated course. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "mTA"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Muerztaler Alps"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Muerztaler Alpen"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
