      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/mDB",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well established name of the elongated depression between the Dachstein group and the Totem Gebirge mountains, which is largely occupied by flat valley floors. Glacial, fluvial and fluvioglacial sediments are involved in its structure, which form gradual transitions to its mountain frame, often consisting of less resistant rocks of the Hallstatt facies. This made the line-sharp delineation difficult and made the inclusion of some isolated elevations of solid rock appear reasonable. A special feature is the drainage in 3 different directions (Grimming to SE, Salza to S and Kainischtraun to NW) and the resulting formation of two valley watersheds in the shallow basin floor. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerte Benennung der langgestreckten, weithin von ebenen Talboeden eingenommenen Senke zwischen Dachsteingruppe und Totem Gebirge. An ihrem Aufbau sind glaziale, fluviale und fluvioglaziale Sedimente beteiligt, die zu ihrer haeufig aus wenig widerstandsfaehigen Gesteinen der Hallstaetter Fazies bestehenden Gebirgsumrahmung weithin allmaehliche uebergaenge bilden. Dies erschwerte die linienscharfe Begrenzung und ließ die Einbeziehung einiger isolierter Erhebungen aus Festgestein sinnvoll erscheinen. Als Besonderheit sei die Entwaesserung in 3 verschiedene Richtung (Grimming nach SE, Salza nach S und Kainischtraun nach NW) und die darin begruendete Ausbildung zweier Talwasserscheiden im flachen Beckenboden hervorgehoben. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "mDB"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Mitterndorfer Becken"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Mitterndorfer basin"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/mZP",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Recht gut eingebuergerte Bezeichnung fuer das von glazialen und fluvioglazialen Sedimenten erfuellte Hochtal an der Wasserscheide zwischen Salza und Erlauf, die in der umgebenden Landschaft der Kalkvoralpen (ueberwiegend Waldmittelgebirge) eine topographische und kulturgeographische Sonderstellung innehat. Die Begrenzung bereitet vor allem im S Schwierigkeiten und wurde hier eher großzuegig festgelegt. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "A quite well-established name for the high valley filled with glacial and fluvioglacial sediments at the watershed between the Salza and Erlauf rivers, which occupies a topographical and cultural-geographical special position in the surrounding landscape of the Limestone Prealps (mainly central forest mountains). The boundary presents difficulties, especially in the S region, and was defined rather generously here. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "mZP"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Mariazeller Passlandschaft"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Mariazell pass landscape"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/mET",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name for the sectionally very broadly developed valley of the Enns valley between the southern foot of the Grimming and the entrance to the Gesaeuse. The valley floor is particularly flat and was also filled with lakes several times after the retreat of the glaciation of the Wuerm Cold Period, which caused groundwater conditions that deviated from those of most other main valleys in Styria. Especially in the area around Irdning, which has certain features of an inner-alpine basin, the boundary beyond the actual valley floor was extended relatively far to the gently formed lower slopes of the Niedere Tauern, thus including the prominent elevation of the Kulm near Aigen in this area. Despite its only vague boundary upstream (to W), the Middle Enns Valley (also called Mitterenn Valley) has many independent geographical features. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerte Bezeichnung fuer den abschnittsweise sehr breit entwickelten Talraum des Ennstales zwischen dem Suedfuß des Grimming und dem Gesaeuseeingang. Der Talboden ist besonders flach und war auch mehrfach nach dem Rueckzug der wuermkaltzeitlichen Vergletscherung von Seen erfuellt, was von den meisten uebrigen steirischen Haupttaelern abweichende Grundwasserverhaeltnisse bedingt. Besonders im Bereich um Irdning, der gewisse Zuege eines inneralpinen Beckens taegt, wurde die Begrenzung ueber den eigentlichen Talboden hinaus relativ weit auf die sanft geformten Unterhaenge der Niederen Tauern ausgedehnt und dadurch auch die markante Erhebung des Kulm bei Aigen in dieses Gebiet einbezogen. Trotz seiner nur vagen Begrenzung flußaufwaerts (nach W) hat das Mittlere Ennstal (auch Mitterennstal) viele eigenstaendige geographische Zuege. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "mET"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Mittleres Ennstal"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Middle Ennstal"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/fBA",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name for the east wing of the Styrian Randgebirge in the S of the Muerztal, culminating in Stuhleck, 1782 m. The low mountain range, which only in its highest part exceeds the forest line, consists of crystalline rocks, which have a carbonatic character south of the Middle Muerztal and in the outermost E on larger areas. A subdivision of the area is possible along the deep insertions (Eibeggsattel, Auf der Schanz, Alpl-Waldheimat and Pfaffensattel), but was not carried out due to lack of suitable names for the individual parts. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerte Bezeichnung fuer den Ostfluegel des Steirischen Randgebirges im S des Muerztales, der im Stuhleck, 1782 m, kulminiert. Der Mittelgebirgszug, der nur in seinem hoechsten Teil die Waldgrenze ueberschreitet, besteht aus kristallinen Gesteinen, die suedlich des Mittleren Muerztales und im aeußersten E auf groeßeren Flaechen karbonatischen Charakter haben. Eine Untergliederung des Gebietes ist entlang der tiefen Einsattelungen (Eibeggsattel, Auf der Schanz, Alpl-Waldheimat und Pfaffensattel) moeglich, wurde jedoch mangels geeigneter Namen fuer die einzelnen Teile nicht vollzogen. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "fBA"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Fischbacher Alps"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Fischbacher Alpen"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/nPL",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name for the spacious depression between the Upper Mur Valley in the N (there with the Neumarkter, 894 m, and the Perchauer Sattel, 995 m, two lower crossings) and the catchment area of the Drava (Hoerfeldbach into the Goertschitz Valley to SE, Olsa to the Metnitz to SW). The area formed by the Pleistocene debris-flow glacier and filled with glacial and fluvioglacial sediments, with a gentle relief in the center, separates the Gurktaler from the Seetaler Alps in a very distinctive way, but it is difficult to draw a clear line against them. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerte Bezeichnung fuer die geraeumige Senke zwischen dem Oberen Murtal im N (dorthin mit dem Neumarkter, 894 m, und dem Perchauer Sattel, 995 m, zwei niedere uebergaenge) und dem Einzugsgebiet der Drau (Hoerfeldbach ins Goertschitztal nach SE, Olsa zur Metnitz nach SW). Der vom pleistozaenen Murgletscher ausgestaltete und von glazialen und fluvioglazialen Sedimenten erfuellte Raum mit im Zentrum sanftwelligem Relief trennt die Gurktaler von den Seetaler Alpen zwar sehr markant, ist gegen diese jedoch nur schwierig linienscharf zu begrenzen. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "nPL"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Neumarkter Passlandschaft"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Neumarkter pass landscape"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/fST",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name, which here only refers to the non-alpine, lower part of the river valley (below the breakthrough at Herberstein Castle) (the name Lower Fistritz Valley also seems possible). It is a NW-SE stretched wide valley of fluvial and fluvioperiglacial sediments. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerter Name, der hier nur den ausseralpinen, unteren Teil des Flusstales (unterhalb des Durchbruches bei Schloss Herberstein) bezeichnet (auch die Benennung Unteres Feistritztal erscheint moeglich). Es handelt sich um einen NW-SE gestreckten breiten Talraum aus fluvialen und fluvioperiglazialen Sedimenten. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "fST"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Feistritztal"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Feistritztal"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/aUB",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name of the spacious basin at the confluence of the 3 source rivers of the Traun, bordered by the plateau edges and foothills of the Dachstein group and the Tote Gebirge mountain range. The widely undulating morphological appearance of the basin is characterized by erosion and filling-up forms of the Pleistocene glacial periods and, in the glacial clearing troughs of the Altausseer and Grundlsees, clearly reverts to the mountainous body of the Tote Gebirge. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerte Benennung des geraeumigen, von den Plateauraendern und Vorbergen der Dachsteingruppe und des Toten Gebirges eingefaßten Talkessels am Zusammenfluß der 3 Quellfluesse der Traun. Das weithin wellig-huegelige morphologische Erscheinungsbild des Beckens wird von Abtragungs- und Aufschuettungsformen der pleistozaenen Kaltzeiten gepraegt und greift in den glazialen Ausraeumungswannen des Altausseer und Grundlsees deutlich in den Gebirgskoerper des Toten Gebirges zurueck. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "aUB"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Ausseer Becken"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Ausseer basin"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/pSB",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name for the inner-alpine basin in the catchment area of the Raab river, which is located entirely within the Graz mountain region. The gentle forms in the basin interior are built up by tertiary loose material, but partly also by Paleozoic slates. The boundary is defined by sharp slope bends in the N and SE, but only vaguely possible in the other directions.   (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerter Name fuer das zur Gaenze innerhalb des Grazer Berglandes gelegene inneralpine Becken im Einzugsgebiet der Raab. Die sanften Formen im Beckeninneren werden von tertiaerem Lockermaterial, z.T. aber auch aus palaeozoischen Schiefern aufgebaut. Die Umgrenzung ist im N und SE durch scharfe Hangknicke vorgegeben, nach den uebrigen Richtungen jedoch nur vage moeglich.   (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "pSB"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Passailer Becken"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Passailer basin"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
