  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/lFT",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name, which here refers only to the non-alpine part of the river valley. It is a wide riverbed valley of fluvial and fluvioperiglacial sediments, which at least in parts is still characterized by a comparatively high degree of naturalness. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergter Name, der hier nur den ausseralpinen Teil des Flusstales bezeichnet. Dieser stellt ein breites Sohlental aus fluvialen und fluvioperiglazialen Sedimenten dar, das sich zumindest abschnittsweise noch durch vergleichsweise hohen Natuerlichkeitsgrad auszeichnet. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "lFT"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Lafnitztal"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Lafnitztal"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/sUT",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Well-established name for the non-alpine, lower part of the river valley (the upper reaches of the two source rivers have mountain stream character in canyon-like valleys). It is a wide valley area, composed of fluvial and fluvioperiglacial, and to a lesser extent fluvioglacial sediments, which narrows considerably in two places at the southern edge of the Sausal (sections of the breakthrough valley), the valley widening in between could be separated as a sub-area under the name Heimschuher Becken. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gut eingebuergerter Name fuer den ausseralpinen, unteren Teil des Flusstales (die Oberlaeufe der beiden Quellfluesse haben Gebirgsbachcharakter in schluchtartigen Engtaelern). Es handelt sich um einen breiten, aus fluvialen und fluvioperiglazialen, untergeordnet auch fluvioglazialen Sedimenten aufgebauten Talraum, der sich am Suedrand des Sausals an zwei Stellen stark verengt (Durchbruchstalabschnitte), die Talweitung dazwischen koennte unter der Bezeichnung Heimschuher Becken als Teilgebiet ausgesondert werden. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "sUT"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Sulmtal"
      },
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Sulmtal"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/uET",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Recht gut eingebuergerte Bezeichnung fuer das Ennstal unterhalb des Gesaeuses, die auch noch fuer die groeßeren oberoesterreichischen Anteile ueblich ist. Bedingt durch die Lage unterhalb der Endmoraenen des wuermzeitlichen Ennsgletschers ist das Tal mit maechtigen, weithin konglomerierten fluvioglazialen Schottern erfuellt, in die der Fluss selbst schluchtartig eingetieft ist. Dadurch sind die siedlungstragenden Terrassen stark voneinander isoliert, was die Zusammenfassung zu einem einheitlichen Talraum in gewissem Sinne problematisch macht. Die Begrenzungslinie wurde eher streng, weithin am Oberrand der wuermzeitlichen Fluren, gezogen. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Quite well established name for the Enns valley below the Gesaeuse, which is also still common for the larger Upper Austrian parts. Due to its location below the terminal moraines of the Wuerm Age Enns glacier, the valley is filled with mighty, widely conglomerated fluvioglacial gravel, into which the river itself is deepened like a canyon. The terraces supporting the settlements are thus strongly isolated from each other, which in a certain sense makes it problematic to combine them into a single valley. The boundary line was drawn rather strictly, largely at the upper edge of the Wuerm period corridors. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "uET"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Unteres Ennstal"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Lower Ennstal"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#topConceptOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK/gGB",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/applicationschema/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/subject": [
      {
        "@id": "http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/theme/br"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Wenig eingebuergerte Bezeichnung, oft nur Gratkorner Becken genannt. Das Herzstueck dieses Beckens, das im SW zum Vorland (Weststeirisches Riedelland) hin offen ist, bildet eine weithin von Siedlungs-, Verkehrs- und Industrieflaechen eingenommene Talweitung der Mur mit ausgedehnten fluvialen und fluvioglazialen Akkumulationen. Der oestl. und suedwestl. Teil des Beckens bestehen hingegen aus tertiaerem Lockermaterial und aehneln daher den Riedellaendern des Vorlandes. Im SE von Rein, das in einer seitlichen, selbst beckenartigen Talweitung liegt, mußten auch einige geologisch dem Grazer Bergland zugehoerige Erhebungen einbezogen werden. (Verfasser: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Few established designation, often only ridge-grain basin named. The heart of this basin, which is open in the SW towards the foreland (West Styrian Riedelland), is a valley extension of the Mur, largely occupied by settlement, traffic and industrial areas, with extensive fluvial and fluvioglacial accumulations. The eastern and southwestern part of the basin consists of tertiary loose material and is therefore similar to the reedlands of the foreland. In the SE of Rein, which lies in a lateral, even basin-like valley widening, some geologically associated elevations of the Graz highlands had to be included. (Author: Prof. Mag. Dr. Gerhard Karl LIEB)"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme": [
      {
        "@id": "https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/NaturraumregionenSTMK"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation": [
      {
        "@value": "gGB"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel": [
      {
        "@language": "de",
        "@value": "Gratwein-Gratkorner Becken"
      },
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Gratwein-Gratkorner basin"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "INSPIRE governance level: national-technical"
      }
    ],
